5654// This headers provides the `isatty()`/`fileno()` functions,
5655// which are used for testing whether a standart stream refers
5656// to the terminal. As for Windows, we also need WinApi funcs
5657// for changing colors attributes of the terminal.
5658#if defined(TERMCOLOR_OS_MACOS) || defined(TERMCOLOR_OS_LINUX)
5659
5660#include <unistd.h>
5661
5662#elif defined(TERMCOLOR_OS_WINDOWS)
5663#include <io.h>
5664#include <windows.h>
5665#endif
5666
5667#include <cstdio>
5668#include <iostream>
5669
5670namespace termcolor {
5671// Forward declaration of the `_internal` namespace.
5672// All comments are below.
5673 namespace _internal {
5674// An index to be used to access a private storage of I/O streams. See
5675// colorize / nocolorize I/O manipulators for details.
5676 static int colorize_index = std::ios_base::xalloc();
5677
5678 inline FILE *get_standard_stream(const std::ostream &stream);
5679
5680 inline bool is_colorized(std::ostream &stream);
5681
5682 inline bool is_atty(const std::ostream &stream);
5683
5684#if defined(TERMCOLOR_OS_WINDOWS)
5685 inline void win_change_attributes(std::ostream &stream, int foreground, int background = -1);
5686#endif
5687 } // namespace _internal
5688
5689 inline std::ostream &colorize(std::ostream &stream) {
5690 stream.iword(_internal::colorize_index) = 1L;
5691 return stream;
5692 }
5693
5694 inline std::ostream &nocolorize(std::ostream &stream) {
5695 stream.iword(_internal::colorize_index) = 0L;
5696 return stream;
5697 }
5698
5699 inline std::ostream &reset(std::ostream &stream) {
5700 if (_internal::is_colorized(stream)) {
5701#if defined(TERMCOLOR_OS_MACOS) || defined(TERMCOLOR_OS_LINUX)
5702 stream << "\033[00m";
5703#elif defined(TERMCOLOR_OS_WINDOWS)
5704 _internal::win_change_attributes(stream, -1, -1);
5705#endif
5706 }
5707 return stream;
5708 }

5880 inline std::ostream &on_grey(std::ostream &stream) {
5881 if (_internal::is_colorized(stream)) {
5882#if defined(TERMCOLOR_OS_MACOS) || defined(TERMCOLOR_OS_LINUX)
5883 stream << "\033[40m";
5884#elif defined(TERMCOLOR_OS_WINDOWS)
5885 _internal::win_change_attributes(stream, -1,
5886 0 // grey (black)
5887 );
5888#endif
5889 }
5890 return stream;
5891 }
5892

5894 if (_internal::is_colorized(stream)) {
5895#if defined(TERMCOLOR_OS_MACOS) || defined(TERMCOLOR_OS_LINUX)
5896 stream << "\033[41m";
5897#elif defined(TERMCOLOR_OS_WINDOWS)
5898 _internal::win_change_attributes(stream, -1, BACKGROUND_RED);
5899#endif
5900 }
5901 return stream;
5902 }

5971
5976 namespace _internal {
5980 inline FILE *get_standard_stream(const std::ostream &stream) {
5981 if (&stream == &std::cout)
5982 return stdout;
5983 else if ((&stream == &std::cerr) || (&stream == &std::clog))
5984 return stderr;
5985
5986 return 0;
5987 }
5988
5989// Say whether a given stream should be colorized or not. It's always
5990// true for ATTY streams and may be true for streams marked with
5991// colorize flag.
5992 inline bool is_colorized(std::ostream &stream) {
5993 return is_atty(stream) || static_cast<bool>(stream.iword(colorize_index));
5994 }
5995
5998 inline bool is_atty(const std::ostream &stream) {
5999 FILE *std_stream = get_standard_stream(stream);
6000
6001 // Unfortunately, fileno() ends with segmentation fault
6002 // if invalid file descriptor is passed. So we need to
6003 // handle this case gracefully and assume it's not a tty
6004 // if standard stream is not detected, and 0 is returned.
6005 if (!std_stream)
6006 return false;
6007
6008#if defined(TERMCOLOR_OS_MACOS) || defined(TERMCOLOR_OS_LINUX)
6009 return ::isatty(fileno(std_stream));
6010#elif defined(TERMCOLOR_OS_WINDOWS)
6011 return ::_isatty(_fileno(std_stream));
6012#endif
6013 }
6014
6015#if defined(TERMCOLOR_OS_WINDOWS)
6018 inline void win_change_attributes(std::ostream &stream, int foreground, int background) {
6019 // yeah, i know.. it's ugly, it's windows.
6020 static WORD defaultAttributes = 0;
6021
6022 // Windows doesn't have ANSI escape sequences and so we use special
6023 // API to change Terminal output color. That means we can't
6024 // manipulate colors by means of "std::stringstream" and hence
6025 // should do nothing in this case.
6026 if (!_internal::is_atty(stream))
6027 return;
6028
6029 // get terminal handle
6030 HANDLE hTerminal = INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE;
6031 if (&stream == &std::cout)
6032 hTerminal = GetStdHandle(STD_OUTPUT_HANDLE);
6033 else if (&stream == &std::cerr)
6034 hTerminal = GetStdHandle(STD_ERROR_HANDLE);
6035
6036 // save default terminal attributes if it unsaved
6037 if (!defaultAttributes) {
6038 CONSOLE_SCREEN_BUFFER_INFO info;
6039 if (!GetConsoleScreenBufferInfo(hTerminal, &info))
6040 return;
6041 defaultAttributes = info.wAttributes;
6042 }
6043
6044 // restore all default settings
6045 if (foreground == -1 && background == -1) {
6046 SetConsoleTextAttribute(hTerminal, defaultAttributes);
6047 return;
6048 }
6049
6050 // get current settings
6051 CONSOLE_SCREEN_BUFFER_INFO info;
6052 if (!GetConsoleScreenBufferInfo(hTerminal, &info))
6053 return;
6054
6055 if (foreground != -1) {
6056 info.wAttributes &= ~(info.wAttributes & 0x0F);
6057 info.wAttributes |= static_cast<WORD>(foreground);
6058 }
6059
6060 if (background != -1) {
6061 info.wAttributes &= ~(info.wAttributes & 0xF0);
6062 info.wAttributes |= static_cast<WORD>(background);
6063 }
6064
6065 SetConsoleTextAttribute(hTerminal, info.wAttributes);
6066 }
6067#endif // TERMCOLOR_OS_WINDOWS
6068
6069 } // namespace _internal
6070
6071} // namespace termcolor
6072
6073#undef TERMCOLOR_OS_WINDOWS
6074#undef TERMCOLOR_OS_MACOS
6075#undef TERMCOLOR_OS_LINUX
6076
6077#endif // TERMCOLOR_HPP_

6115#include <string>

6117#include <clocale>

6122#include <wchar.h>

6124namespace tabulate {
6125
6126#if defined(__unix__) || defined(__unix) || defined(__APPLE__)
6127
6128 inline int get_wcswidth(const std::string &string, const std::string &locale,
6129 size_t max_column_width) {
6130 if (string.size() == 0)
6131 return 0;
6132
6133 // The behavior of wcswidth() depends on the LC_CTYPE category of the current locale.
6134 // Set the current locale based on cell properties before computing width
6135 auto old_locale = std::locale::global(std::locale(locale));
6136
6137 // Convert from narrow std::string to wide string
6138 wchar_t *wide_string = new wchar_t[string.size()];
6139 std::mbstowcs(wide_string, string.c_str(), string.size());
6140
6141 // Compute display width of wide string
6142 int result = wcswidth(wide_string, max_column_width);
6143 delete[] wide_string;
6144
6145 // Restore old locale
6146 std::locale::global(old_locale);
6147
6148 return result;
6149 }
6150
6151#endif
6152
6153 inline size_t get_sequence_length(const std::string &text, const std::string &locale,
6154 bool is_multi_byte_character_support_enabled) {
6155 if (!is_multi_byte_character_support_enabled)
6156 return text.length();
6157
6158#if defined(_WIN32) || defined(_WIN64)
6159 return (text.length() - std::count_if(text.begin(), text.end(),
6160 [](char c) -> bool { return (c & 0xC0) == 0x80; }));
6161#elif defined(__unix__) || defined(__unix) || defined(__APPLE__)
6162 auto result = get_wcswidth(text, locale, text.size());
6163 if (result >= 0)
6164 return result;
6165 else
6166 return (text.length() - std::count_if(text.begin(), text.end(),
6167 [](char c) -> bool { return (c & 0xC0) == 0x80; }));
6168#endif
6169 }
6170
6171} // namespace tabulate

6719
6720 // Apply word wrap
6721 // Given an input string and a line length, this will insert \n
6722 // in strategic places in input string and apply word wrapping
6723 static std::string word_wrap(const std::string &str, size_t width, const std::string &locale,
6724 bool is_multi_byte_character_support_enabled) {
6725 std::vector<std::string> words = explode_string(str, {" ", "-", "\t"});
6726 size_t current_line_length = 0;
6727 std::string result;
6728
6729 for (size_t i = 0; i < words.size(); ++i) {
6730 std::string word = words[i];
6731 // If adding the new word to the current line would be too long,
6732 // then put it on a new line (and split it up if it's too long).
6733 if (current_line_length +
6734 get_sequence_length(word, locale, is_multi_byte_character_support_enabled) >
6735 width) {
6736 // Only move down to a new line if we have text on the current line.
6737 // Avoids situation where wrapped whitespace causes emptylines in text.
6738 if (current_line_length > 0) {
6739 result += '\n';
6740 current_line_length = 0;
6741 }
6742
6743 // If the current word is too long to fit on a line even on it's own then
6744 // split the word up.
6745 while (get_sequence_length(word, locale, is_multi_byte_character_support_enabled) > width) {
6746 result += word.substr(0, width - 1) + "-";
6747 word = word.substr(width - 1);
6748 result += '\n';
6749 }
6750
6751 // Remove leading whitespace from the word so the new line starts flush to the left.
6752 word = trim_left(word);
6753 }
6754 result += word;
6755 current_line_length +=
6756 get_sequence_length(word, locale, is_multi_byte_character_support_enabled);
6757 }
6758 return result;
6759 }
6760
6761 static std::vector<std::string> split_lines(const std::string &text, const std::string &delimiter,
6762 const std::string &locale,
6763 bool is_multi_byte_character_support_enabled) {
6764 std::vector<std::string> result{};
6765 std::string input = text;
6766 size_t pos = 0;
6767 std::string token;
6768 while ((pos = input.find(delimiter)) != std::string::npos) {
6769 token = input.substr(0, pos);
6770 result.push_back(token);
6771 input.erase(0, pos + delimiter.length());
6772 }
6773 if (get_sequence_length(input, locale, is_multi_byte_character_support_enabled))
6774 result.push_back(input);
6775 return result;
6776 };
6777
6778 // Merge two formats
6779 // first has higher precedence
6780 // e.g., first = cell-level formatting and
6781 // second = row-level formatting
6782 // Result has attributes of both with cell-level
6783 // formatting taking precedence
6784 static Format merge(Format first, Format second) {
6785 Format result;
6786
6787 // Width and height
6788 if (first.width_.has_value())
6789 result.width_ = first.width_;
6790 else
6791 result.width_ = second.width_;
6792
6793 if (first.height_.has_value())
6794 result.height_ = first.height_;
6795 else
6796 result.height_ = second.height_;
6797
6798 // Font styling
6799 if (first.font_align_.has_value())
6800 result.font_align_ = first.font_align_;
6801 else
6802 result.font_align_ = second.font_align_;
6803
6804 if (first.font_style_.has_value()) {
6805 // Merge font styles using std::set_union
6806 std::vector<FontStyle> merged_font_style(first.font_style_->size() +
6807 second.font_style_->size());
6808#if defined(_WIN32) || defined(_WIN64)
6809 // Fixes error in Windows - Sequence not ordered
6810 std::sort(first.font_style_->begin(), first.font_style_->end());
6811 std::sort(second.font_style_->begin(), second.font_style_->end());
6812#endif
6813 std::set_union(first.font_style_->begin(), first.font_style_->end(),
6814 second.font_style_->begin(), second.font_style_->end(),
6815 merged_font_style.begin());
6816 result.font_style_ = merged_font_style;
6817 } else
6818 result.font_style_ = second.font_style_;
6819
6820 if (first.font_color_.has_value())
6821 result.font_color_ = first.font_color_;
6822 else
6823 result.font_color_ = second.font_color_;
6824
6825 if (first.font_background_color_.has_value())
6826 result.font_background_color_ = first.font_background_color_;
6827 else
6828 result.font_background_color_ = second.font_background_color_;
6829
6830 // Padding
6831 if (first.padding_left_.has_value())

6833 else
6834 result.padding_left_ = second.padding_left_;
6835
6836 if (first.padding_top_.has_value())

6838 else

6848 else

6859 else
6860 result.border_left_color_ = second.border_left_color_;
6861
6862 if (first.border_left_background_color_.has_value())
6863 result.border_left_background_color_ = first.border_left_background_color_;
6864 else
6865 result.border_left_background_color_ = second.border_left_background_color_;
6866
6867 if (first.border_top_.has_value())
6868 result.border_top_ = first.border_top_;
6869 else
6870 result.border_top_ = second.border_top_;
6871

6874 else
6875 result.border_top_color_ = second.border_top_color_;

6879 else
6880 result.border_top_background_color_ = second.border_top_background_color_;
6881
6882 if (first.border_bottom_.has_value())
6883 result.border_bottom_ = first.border_bottom_;
6884 else

6886
6887 if (first.border_bottom_color_.has_value())
6888 result.border_bottom_color_ = first.border_bottom_color_;
6889 else
6890 result.border_bottom_color_ = second.border_bottom_color_;

7063
7064 // Helper methods for word wrapping:
7065
7066 // trim white spaces from the left end of an input string
7067 static std::string trim_left(const std::string &input_string) {
7068 std::string result = input_string;
7069 result.erase(result.begin(), std::find_if(result.begin(), result.end(),
7070 [](int ch) { return !std::isspace(ch); }));
7071 return result;
7072 }
7073
7074 // trim white spaces from right end of an input string
7075 static std::string trim_right(const std::string &input_string) {
7076 std::string result = input_string;
7077 result.erase(
7078 std::find_if(result.rbegin(), result.rend(), [](int ch) { return !std::isspace(ch); })
7079 .base(),
7080 result.end());
7081 return result;
7082 }
7083
7084 // trim white spaces from either end of an input string
7085 static std::string trim(const std::string &input_string) {
7086 return trim_left(trim_right(input_string));
7087 }
7088
7089 static size_t index_of_any(const std::string &input, size_t start_index,
7090 const std::vector<std::string> &split_characters) {
7091 std::vector<size_t> indices{};
7092 for (auto &c: split_characters) {
7093 auto index = input.find(c, start_index);
7094 if (index != std::string::npos)
7095 indices.push_back(index);
7096 }
7097 if (indices.size() > 0)
7098 return *std::min_element(indices.begin(), indices.end());
7099 else
7100 return std::string::npos;
7101 }
7102
7103 static std::vector<std::string> explode_string(const std::string &input,
7104 const std::vector<std::string> &split_characters) {
7105 std::vector<std::string> result{};
7106 size_t start_index{0};
7107 while (true) {
7108 auto index = index_of_any(input, start_index, split_characters);
7109
7110 if (index == std::string::npos) {
7111 result.push_back(input.substr(start_index));
7112 return result;
7113 }
7114
7115 std::string word = input.substr(start_index, index - start_index);
7116 char next_character = input.substr(index, 1)[0];
7117 // Unlike whitespace, dashes and the like should stick to the word occurring before it.
7118 if (isspace(next_character)) {
7119 result.push_back(word);
7120 result.push_back(std::string(1, next_character));
7121 } else {
7122 result.push_back(word + next_character);
7123 }
7124 start_index = index + 1;
7125 }
7126
7127 return result;
7128 }

7222 }
7223
7224 std::string locale() { return *format().locale_; }
7225
7226 Format &format();
7227
7228 bool is_multi_byte_character_support_enabled();
7229
7230 private:
7231 std::string data_;
7232 std::weak_ptr<class Row> parent_;
7233 optional<Format> format_;
7234 };
7235
7236} // namespace tabulate

7291#endif

7293#undef min
7294#endif

7296namespace tabulate {
7297
7298 class Row {
7299 public:
7300 explicit Row(std::shared_ptr<class TableInternal> parent) : parent_(parent) {}
7301
7302 void add_cell(std::shared_ptr<Cell> cell) { cells_.push_back(cell); }
7303
7304 Cell &operator[](size_t index) { return cell(index); }
7305
7306 Cell &cell(size_t index) { return *(cells_[index]); }
7307
7308 std::vector<std::shared_ptr<Cell>> cells() const { return cells_; }
7309
7310 size_t size() const { return cells_.size(); }
7311
7312 Format &format();
7313
7314 class CellIterator {
7315 public:
7316 explicit CellIterator(std::vector<std::shared_ptr<Cell>>::iterator ptr) : ptr(ptr) {}
7317
7318 CellIterator operator++() {
7319 ++ptr;
7320 return *this;
7321 }
7322
7323 bool operator!=(const CellIterator &other) const { return ptr != other.ptr; }
7324
7325 Cell &operator*() { return **ptr; }
7326
7327 private:
7328 std::vector<std::shared_ptr<Cell>>::iterator ptr;
7329 };
7330
7331 auto begin() -> CellIterator { return CellIterator(cells_.begin()); }
7332
7333 auto end() -> CellIterator { return CellIterator(cells_.end()); }
7334
7335 private:
7336 friend class Printer;
7337
7338 // Returns the row height as configured
7339 // For each cell in the row, check the cell.format.height
7340 // property and return the largest configured row height
7341 // This is used to ensure that all cells in a row are
7342 // aligned when printing the column
7343 size_t get_configured_height() {
7344 size_t result{0};
7345 for (size_t i = 0; i < size(); ++i) {
7346 auto cell = cells_[i];
7347 auto format = cell->format();
7348 if (format.height_.has_value())
7349 result = std::max(result, *format.height_);
7350 }
7351 return result;
7352 }
7353
7354 // Computes the height of the row based on cell contents
7355 // and configured cell padding
7356 // For each cell, compute:
7357 // padding_top + (cell_contents / column height) + padding_bottom
7358 // and return the largest value
7359 //
7360 // This is useful when no cell.format.height is configured
7361 // Call get_configured_height()
7362 // - If this returns 0, then use get_computed_height()
7363 size_t get_computed_height(const std::vector<size_t> &column_widths) {
7364 size_t result{0};
7365 for (size_t i = 0; i < size(); ++i) {
7366 result = std::max(result, get_cell_height(i, column_widths[i]));
7367 }
7368 return result;
7369 }
7370
7371 // Returns padding_top + cell_contents / column_height + padding_bottom
7372 // for a given cell in the column
7373 // e.g.,
7374 // column width = 5
7375 // cell_contents = "I love tabulate" (size/length = 15)
7376 // padding top and padding bottom are 1
7377 // then, cell height = 1 + (15 / 5) + 1 = 1 + 3 + 1 = 5
7378 // The cell will look like this:
7379 //
7380 // .....
7381 // I lov
7382 // e tab
7383 // ulate
7384 // .....
7385 size_t get_cell_height(size_t cell_index, size_t column_width) {
7386 size_t result{0};
7387 Cell &cell = *(cells_[cell_index]);
7388 auto format = cell.format();
7389 auto text = cell.get_text();
7390
7391 auto padding_left = *format.padding_left_;
7392 auto padding_right = *format.padding_right_;
7393
7394 result += *format.padding_top_;
7395
7396 if (column_width > (padding_left + padding_right)) {
7397 column_width -= (padding_left + padding_right);
7398 }
7399
7400 // Check if input text has embedded newline characters
7401 auto newlines_in_text = std::count(text.begin(), text.end(), '\n');
7402 std::string word_wrapped_text;
7403 if (newlines_in_text == 0) {
7404 // No new lines in input
7405 // Apply automatic word wrapping and compute row height
7406 word_wrapped_text = Format::word_wrap(text, column_width, cell.locale(),
7407 cell.is_multi_byte_character_support_enabled());
7408 } else {
7409 // There are embedded '\n' characters
7410 // Respect these characters
7411 word_wrapped_text = text;
7412 }
7413
7414 auto newlines_in_wrapped_text =
7415 std::count(word_wrapped_text.begin(), word_wrapped_text.end(), '\n');
7416 auto estimated_row_height = newlines_in_wrapped_text;
7417
7418 if (!word_wrapped_text.empty() &&
7419 word_wrapped_text[word_wrapped_text.size() - 1] != '\n') // text doesn't end with a newline
7420 estimated_row_height += 1;
7421
7422 result += estimated_row_height;
7423
7424 result += *format.padding_bottom_;
7425
7426 return result;
7427 }
7428
7429 std::vector<std::shared_ptr<Cell>> cells_;
7430 std::weak_ptr<class TableInternal> parent_;
7431 optional<Format> format_;
7432 };
7433
7434} // namespace tabulate

7592#pragma once
7593
7594#include <algorithm>
7595#include <functional>
7596#include <iostream>
7597#include <memory>
7598#include <optional>
7599#include <string>
7600// #include <tabulate/cell.hpp>
7601// #include <tabulate/column_format.hpp>
7602#include <vector>
7603
7604#ifdef max
7605#undef max
7606#endif
7607#ifdef min
7608#undef min
7609#endif
7610
7611namespace tabulate {
7612
7613 class Column {
7614 public:
7615 explicit Column(std::shared_ptr<class TableInternal> parent) : parent_(parent) {}
7616
7617 void add_cell(Cell &cell) { cells_.push_back(cell); }
7618
7619 Cell &operator[](size_t index) { return cells_[index]; }
7620
7621 std::vector<std::reference_wrapper<Cell>> cells() const { return cells_; }
7622
7623 size_t size() const { return cells_.size(); }
7624
7625 ColumnFormat format() { return ColumnFormat(*this); }
7626
7627 class CellIterator {
7628 public:
7629 explicit CellIterator(std::vector<std::reference_wrapper<Cell>>::iterator ptr) : ptr(ptr) {}
7630
7631 CellIterator operator++() {
7632 ++ptr;
7633 return *this;
7634 }
7635
7636 bool operator!=(const CellIterator &other) const { return ptr != other.ptr; }
7637
7638 Cell &operator*() { return *ptr; }
7639
7640 private:
7641 std::vector<std::reference_wrapper<Cell>>::iterator ptr;
7642 };
7643
7644 auto begin() -> CellIterator { return CellIterator(cells_.begin()); }
7645
7646 auto end() -> CellIterator { return CellIterator(cells_.end()); }
7647
7648 private:
7649 friend class ColumnFormat;
7650
7651 friend class Printer;
7652
7653 // Returns the column width as configured
7654 // For each cell in the column, check the cell.format.width
7655 // property and return the largest configured column width
7656 // This is used to ensure that all cells in a column are
7657 // aligned when printing the column
7658 size_t get_configured_width() {
7659 size_t result{0};
7660 for (size_t i = 0; i < size(); ++i) {
7661 auto cell = cells_[i];
7662 auto format = cell.get().format();
7663 if (format.width_.has_value())
7664 result = std::max(result, *format.width_);
7665 }
7666 return result;
7667 }
7668
7669 // Computes the width of the column based on cell contents
7670 // and configured cell padding
7671 // For each cell, compute padding_left + cell_contents + padding_right
7672 // and return the largest value
7673 //
7674 // This is useful when no cell.format.width is configured
7675 // Call get_configured_width()
7676 // - If this returns 0, then use get_computed_width()
7677 size_t get_computed_width() {
7678 size_t result{0};
7679 for (size_t i = 0; i < size(); ++i) {
7680 result = std::max(result, get_cell_width(i));
7681 }
7682 return result;
7683 }
7684
7685 // Returns padding_left + cell_contents.size() + padding_right
7686 // for a given cell in the column
7687 size_t get_cell_width(size_t cell_index) {
7688 size_t result{0};
7689 Cell &cell = cells_[cell_index].get();
7690 auto format = cell.format();
7691 if (format.padding_left_.has_value())
7692 result += *format.padding_left_;
7693
7694 // Check if input text has newlines
7695 auto text = cell.get_text();
7696 auto split_lines = Format::split_lines(text, "\n", cell.locale(),
7697 cell.is_multi_byte_character_support_enabled());
7698
7699 // If there are no newlines in input, set column_width = text.size()
7700 if (split_lines.size() == 1) {
7701 result += cell.size();
7702 } else {
7703 // There are newlines in input
7704 // Find widest substring in input and use this as column_width
7705 size_t widest_sub_string_size{0};
7706 for (auto &line: split_lines)
7707 if (get_sequence_length(line, cell.locale(),
7708 cell.is_multi_byte_character_support_enabled()) >
7709 widest_sub_string_size)
7710 widest_sub_string_size = get_sequence_length(
7711 line, cell.locale(), cell.is_multi_byte_character_support_enabled());
7712 result += widest_sub_string_size;
7713 }
7714
7715 if (format.padding_right_.has_value())
7716 result += *format.padding_right_;
7717
7718 return result;
7719 }
7720
7721 std::vector<std::reference_wrapper<Cell>> cells_;
7722 std::weak_ptr<class TableInternal> parent_;
7723 };

7923 inline ColumnFormat &ColumnFormat::background_color(Color value) {
7924 for (auto &cell: column_.get().cells_)
7925 cell.get().format().background_color(value);
7926 return *this;
7927 }
7928
7929 inline ColumnFormat &ColumnFormat::multi_byte_characters(bool value) {
7930 for (auto &cell: column_.get().cells_)
7931 cell.get().format().multi_byte_characters(value);
7932 return *this;
7933 }
7934
7935 inline ColumnFormat &ColumnFormat::locale(const std::string &value) {
7936 for (auto &cell: column_.get().cells_)
7937 cell.get().format().locale(value);
7938 return *this;
7939 }
7940
7941} // namespace tabulate

7975#pragma once
7976// #include <tabulate/color.hpp>
7977// #include <tabulate/font_style.hpp>
7978#include <utility>
7979#include <vector>

7981namespace tabulate {
7982
7983 class Printer {
7984 public:
7985 static std::pair<std::vector<size_t>, std::vector<size_t>>
7986 compute_cell_dimensions(TableInternal &table);
7987
7988 static void print_table(std::ostream &stream, TableInternal &table);
7989
7990 static void print_row_in_cell(std::ostream &stream, TableInternal &table,
7991 const std::pair<size_t, size_t> &index,
7992 const std::pair<size_t, size_t> &dimension, size_t num_columns,
7993 size_t row_index);
7994
7995 static bool print_cell_border_top(std::ostream &stream, TableInternal &table,
7996 const std::pair<size_t, size_t> &index,
7997 const std::pair<size_t, size_t> &dimension, size_t num_columns);
7998
7999 static bool print_cell_border_bottom(std::ostream &stream, TableInternal &table,
8000 const std::pair<size_t, size_t> &index,
8001 const std::pair<size_t, size_t> &dimension,
8002 size_t num_columns);
8003
8004 static void apply_element_style(std::ostream &stream, Color foreground_color,
8005 Color background_color,
8006 const std::vector<FontStyle> &font_style) {
8007 apply_foreground_color(stream, foreground_color);
8008 apply_background_color(stream, background_color);
8009 for (auto &style: font_style)
8010 apply_font_style(stream, style);
8011 }
8012
8013 static void reset_element_style(std::ostream &stream) { stream << termcolor::reset; }
8014
8015 private:
8016 static void print_content_left_aligned(std::ostream &stream, const std::string &cell_content,
8017 const Format &format, size_t text_with_padding_size,
8018 size_t column_width) {
8019
8020 // Apply font style
8021 apply_element_style(stream, *format.font_color_, *format.font_background_color_,
8022 *format.font_style_);
8023 stream << cell_content;
8024 // Only apply font_style to the font
8025 // Not the padding. So calling apply_element_style with font_style = {}
8026 reset_element_style(stream);
8027 apply_element_style(stream, *format.font_color_, *format.font_background_color_, {});
8028
8029 if (text_with_padding_size < column_width) {
8030 for (size_t j = 0; j < (column_width - text_with_padding_size); ++j) {
8031 stream << " ";
8032 }
8033 }
8034 }
8035
8036 static void print_content_center_aligned(std::ostream &stream, const std::string &cell_content,
8037 const Format &format, size_t text_with_padding_size,
8038 size_t column_width) {
8039 auto num_spaces = column_width - text_with_padding_size;
8040 if (num_spaces % 2 == 0) {
8041 // Even spacing on either side
8042 for (size_t j = 0; j < num_spaces / 2; ++j)
8043 stream << " ";
8044
8045 // Apply font style
8046 apply_element_style(stream, *format.font_color_, *format.font_background_color_,
8047 *format.font_style_);
8048 stream << cell_content;
8049 // Only apply font_style to the font
8050 // Not the padding. So calling apply_element_style with font_style = {}
8051 reset_element_style(stream);
8052 apply_element_style(stream, *format.font_color_, *format.font_background_color_, {});
8053
8054 for (size_t j = 0; j < num_spaces / 2; ++j)
8055 stream << " ";
8056 } else {
8057 auto num_spaces_before = num_spaces / 2 + 1;
8058 for (size_t j = 0; j < num_spaces_before; ++j)
8059 stream << " ";
8060
8061 // Apply font style
8062 apply_element_style(stream, *format.font_color_, *format.font_background_color_,
8063 *format.font_style_);
8064 stream << cell_content;
8065 // Only apply font_style to the font
8066 // Not the padding. So calling apply_element_style with font_style = {}
8067 reset_element_style(stream);
8068 apply_element_style(stream, *format.font_color_, *format.font_background_color_, {});
8069
8070 for (size_t j = 0; j < num_spaces - num_spaces_before; ++j)
8071 stream << " ";
8072 }
8073 }
8074
8075 static void print_content_right_aligned(std::ostream &stream, const std::string &cell_content,
8076 const Format &format, size_t text_with_padding_size,
8077 size_t column_width) {
8078 if (text_with_padding_size < column_width) {
8079 for (size_t j = 0; j < (column_width - text_with_padding_size); ++j) {
8080 stream << " ";
8081 }
8082 }
8083
8084 // Apply font style
8085 apply_element_style(stream, *format.font_color_, *format.font_background_color_,
8086 *format.font_style_);
8087 stream << cell_content;
8088 // Only apply font_style to the font
8089 // Not the padding. So calling apply_element_style with font_style = {}
8090 reset_element_style(stream);
8091 apply_element_style(stream, *format.font_color_, *format.font_background_color_, {});
8092 }
8093
8094 static void apply_font_style(std::ostream &stream, FontStyle style) {
8095 switch (style) {
8096 case FontStyle::bold:
8097 stream << termcolor::bold;
8098 break;
8099 case FontStyle::dark:
8100 stream << termcolor::dark;
8101 break;
8102 case FontStyle::italic:
8103 stream << termcolor::italic;
8104 break;
8105 case FontStyle::underline:
8106 stream << termcolor::underline;
8107 break;
8108 case FontStyle::blink:
8109 stream << termcolor::blink;
8110 break;
8111 case FontStyle::reverse:
8112 stream << termcolor::reverse;
8113 break;
8114 case FontStyle::concealed:
8115 stream << termcolor::concealed;
8116 break;
8117 case FontStyle::crossed:
8118 stream << termcolor::crossed;
8119 break;
8120 default:
8121 break;
8122 }
8123 }
8124
8125 static void apply_foreground_color(std::ostream &stream, Color foreground_color) {
8126 switch (foreground_color) {
8127 case Color::grey:
8128 stream << termcolor::grey;
8129 break;
8130 case Color::red:
8131 stream << termcolor::red;
8132 break;
8133 case Color::green:
8134 stream << termcolor::green;
8135 break;
8136 case Color::yellow:
8137 stream << termcolor::yellow;
8138 break;
8139 case Color::blue:
8140 stream << termcolor::blue;
8141 break;
8142 case Color::magenta:
8143 stream << termcolor::magenta;
8144 break;
8145 case Color::cyan:
8146 stream << termcolor::cyan;
8147 break;
8148 case Color::white:
8149 stream << termcolor::white;
8150 break;
8151 case Color::none:
8152 default:
8153 break;
8154 }
8155 }
8156
8157 static void apply_background_color(std::ostream &stream, Color background_color) {
8158 switch (background_color) {
8159 case Color::grey:
8160 stream << termcolor::on_grey;
8161 break;
8162 case Color::red:
8163 stream << termcolor::on_red;
8164 break;
8165 case Color::green:
8166 stream << termcolor::on_green;
8167 break;
8168 case Color::yellow:
8169 stream << termcolor::on_yellow;
8170 break;
8171 case Color::blue:
8172 stream << termcolor::on_blue;
8173 break;
8174 case Color::magenta:
8175 stream << termcolor::on_magenta;
8176 break;
8177 case Color::cyan:
8178 stream << termcolor::on_cyan;
8179 break;
8180 case Color::white:
8181 stream << termcolor::on_white;
8182 break;
8183 case Color::none:
8184 default:
8185 break;
8186 }
8187 }
8188 };
8189
8190} // namespace tabulate

8226#include <algorithm>
8227#include <iostream>

8229// #include <tabulate/column.hpp>
8230// #include <tabulate/font_style.hpp>

8243namespace tabulate {
8244
8245 class TableInternal : public std::enable_shared_from_this<TableInternal> {
8246 public:
8247 static std::shared_ptr<TableInternal> create() {
8248 auto result = std::shared_ptr<TableInternal>(new TableInternal());
8249 result->format_.set_defaults();
8250 return result;
8251 }
8252
8253 void add_row(const std::vector<std::string> &cells) {
8254 auto row = std::make_shared<Row>(shared_from_this());
8255 for (auto &c: cells) {
8256 auto cell = std::make_shared<Cell>(row);
8257 cell->set_text(c);
8258 row->add_cell(cell);
8259 }
8260 rows_.push_back(row);
8261 }
8262
8263 Row &operator[](size_t index) { return *(rows_[index]); }
8264
8265 const Row &operator[](size_t index) const { return *(rows_[index]); }
8266
8267 Column column(size_t index) {
8268 Column column(shared_from_this());
8269 for (size_t i = 0; i < rows_.size(); ++i) {
8270 auto row = rows_[i];
8271 auto &cell = row->cell(index);
8272 column.add_cell(cell);
8273 }
8274 return column;
8275 }
8276
8277 size_t size() const { return rows_.size(); }
8278
8279 std::pair<size_t, size_t> shape() {
8280 std::pair<size_t, size_t> result{0, 0};
8281 std::stringstream stream;
8282 print(stream);
8283 auto buffer = stream.str();
8284 auto lines = Format::split_lines(buffer, "\n", "", true);
8285 if (lines.size()) {
8286 result = {get_sequence_length(lines[0], "", true), lines.size()};
8287 }
8288 return result;
8289 }
8290
8291 Format &format() { return format_; }
8292
8293 void print(std::ostream &stream) { Printer::print_table(stream, *this); }
8294
8295 size_t estimate_num_columns() const {
8296 size_t result{0};
8297 if (size()) {
8298 auto first_row = operator[](size_t(0));
8299 result = first_row.size();
8300 }
8301 return result;
8302 }
8303
8304 private:
8305 friend class Table;
8306
8307 friend class MarkdownExporter;
8308
8309 TableInternal() {}
8310
8311 TableInternal &operator=(const TableInternal &);
8312
8313 TableInternal(const TableInternal &);
8314
8315 std::vector<std::shared_ptr<Row>> rows_;
8316 Format format_;
8317 };
8318
8319 inline Format &Cell::format() {
8320 std::shared_ptr<Row> parent = parent_.lock();
8321 if (!format_.has_value()) { // no cell format
8322 format_ = parent->format(); // Use parent row format
8323 } else {
8324 // Cell has formatting
8325 // Merge cell formatting with parent row formatting
8326 format_ = Format::merge(*format_, parent->format());
8327 }
8328 return *format_;
8329 }
8330
8331 inline bool Cell::is_multi_byte_character_support_enabled() {
8332 return (*format().multi_byte_characters_);
8333 }
8334
8335 inline Format &Row::format() {
8336 std::shared_ptr<TableInternal> parent = parent_.lock();
8337 if (!format_.has_value()) { // no row format
8338 format_ = parent->format(); // Use parent table format
8339 } else {
8340 // Row has formatting rules
8341 // Merge with parent table format
8342 format_ = Format::merge(*format_, parent->format());
8343 }
8344 return *format_;
8345 }
8346
8347 inline std::pair<std::vector<size_t>, std::vector<size_t>>
8348 Printer::compute_cell_dimensions(TableInternal &table) {
8349 std::pair<std::vector<size_t>, std::vector<size_t>> result;
8350 size_t num_rows = table.size();
8351 size_t num_columns = table.estimate_num_columns();
8352
8353 std::vector<size_t> row_heights, column_widths{};
8354
8355 for (size_t i = 0; i < num_columns; ++i) {
8356 Column column = table.column(i);
8357 size_t configured_width = column.get_configured_width();
8358 size_t computed_width = column.get_computed_width();
8359 if (configured_width != 0)
8360 column_widths.push_back(configured_width);
8361 else
8362 column_widths.push_back(computed_width);
8363 }
8364
8365 for (size_t i = 0; i < num_rows; ++i) {
8366 Row row = table[i];
8367 size_t configured_height = row.get_configured_height();
8368 size_t computed_height = row.get_computed_height(column_widths);
8369
8370 // NOTE: Unlike column width, row height is calculated as the max
8371 // b/w configured height and computed height
8372 // which means that .width() has higher precedence than .height()
8373 // when both are configured by the user
8374 //
8375 // TODO: Maybe this can be configured?
8376 // If such a configuration is exposed, i.e., prefer height over width
8377 // then the logic will be reversed, i.e.,
8378 // column_widths.push_back(std::max(configured_width, computed_width))
8379 // and
8380 // row_height = configured_height if != 0 else computed_height
8381
8382 row_heights.push_back(std::max(configured_height, computed_height));
8383 }
8384
8385 result.first = row_heights;
8386 result.second = column_widths;
8387
8388 return result;
8389 }
8390
8391 inline void Printer::print_table(std::ostream &stream, TableInternal &table) {
8392 size_t num_rows = table.size();
8393 size_t num_columns = table.estimate_num_columns();
8394 auto dimensions = compute_cell_dimensions(table);
8395 auto row_heights = dimensions.first;
8396 auto column_widths = dimensions.second;
8397
8398 // For each row,
8399 for (size_t i = 0; i < num_rows; ++i) {
8400
8401 // Print top border
8402 bool border_top_printed{true};
8403 for (size_t j = 0; j < num_columns; ++j) {
8404 border_top_printed &= print_cell_border_top(stream, table, {i, j},
8405 {row_heights[i], column_widths[j]}, num_columns);
8406 }
8407 if (border_top_printed)
8408 stream << termcolor::reset << "\n";
8409
8410 // Print row contents with word wrapping
8411 for (size_t k = 0; k < row_heights[i]; ++k) {
8412 for (size_t j = 0; j < num_columns; ++j) {
8413 print_row_in_cell(stream, table, {i, j}, {row_heights[i], column_widths[j]}, num_columns,
8414 k);
8415 }
8416 if (k + 1 < row_heights[i])
8417 stream << termcolor::reset << "\n";
8418 }
8419
8420 if (i + 1 == num_rows) {
8421
8422 // Check if there is bottom border to print:
8423 auto bottom_border_needed{true};
8424 for (size_t j = 0; j < num_columns; ++j) {
8425 auto cell = table[i][j];
8426 auto format = cell.format();
8427 auto corner = *format.corner_bottom_left_;
8428 auto border_bottom = *format.border_bottom_;
8429 if (corner == "" && border_bottom == "") {
8430 bottom_border_needed = false;
8431 break;
8432 }
8433 }
8434
8435 if (bottom_border_needed)
8436 stream << termcolor::reset << "\n";
8437 // Print bottom border for table
8438 for (size_t j = 0; j < num_columns; ++j) {
8439 print_cell_border_bottom(stream, table, {i, j}, {row_heights[i], column_widths[j]},
8440 num_columns);
8441 }
8442 }
8443 if (i + 1 < num_rows)
8444 stream << termcolor::reset << "\n"; // Don't add newline after last row
8445 }
8446 }
8447
8448 inline void Printer::print_row_in_cell(std::ostream &stream, TableInternal &table,
8449 const std::pair<size_t, size_t> &index,
8450 const std::pair<size_t, size_t> &dimension,
8451 size_t num_columns, size_t row_index) {
8452 auto column_width = dimension.second;
8453 auto cell = table[index.first][index.second];
8454 auto locale = cell.locale();
8455 auto is_multi_byte_character_support_enabled = cell.is_multi_byte_character_support_enabled();
8456 auto old_locale = std::locale::global(std::locale(locale));
8457 auto format = cell.format();
8458 auto text = cell.get_text();
8459 auto word_wrapped_text =
8460 Format::word_wrap(text, column_width, locale, is_multi_byte_character_support_enabled);
8461 auto text_height = std::count(word_wrapped_text.begin(), word_wrapped_text.end(), '\n') + 1;
8462 auto padding_top = *format.padding_top_;
8463
8464 if (*format.show_border_left_) {
8465 apply_element_style(stream, *format.border_left_color_, *format.border_left_background_color_,
8466 {});
8467 stream << *format.border_left_;
8468 reset_element_style(stream);
8469 }
8470
8471 apply_element_style(stream, *format.font_color_, *format.font_background_color_, {});
8472 if (row_index < padding_top) {
8473 // Padding top
8474 stream << std::string(column_width, ' ');
8475 } else if (row_index >= padding_top && (row_index <= (padding_top + text_height))) {
8476 // // Row contents
8477
8478 // Retrieve padding left and right
8479 // (column_width - padding_left - padding_right) is the amount of space
8480 // available for cell text - Use this to word wrap cell contents
8481 auto padding_left = *format.padding_left_;
8482 auto padding_right = *format.padding_right_;
8483
8484 // Check if input text has embedded \n that are to be respected
8485 auto newlines_in_input = Format::split_lines(text, "\n", cell.locale(),
8486 cell.is_multi_byte_character_support_enabled())
8487 .size() -
8488 1;
8489 std::string word_wrapped_text;
8490
8491 // If there are no embedded \n characters, then apply word wrap
8492 if (newlines_in_input == 0) {
8493 // Apply word wrapping to input text
8494 // Then display one word-wrapped line at a time within cell
8495 if (column_width > (padding_left + padding_right))
8496 word_wrapped_text =
8497 Format::word_wrap(text, column_width - padding_left - padding_right, cell.locale(),
8498 cell.is_multi_byte_character_support_enabled());
8499 else {
8500 // Configured column width cannot be lower than (padding_left + padding_right)
8501 // This is a bad configuration
8502 // E.g., the user is trying to force the column width to be 5
8503 // when padding_left and padding_right are each configured to 3
8504 // (padding_left + padding_right) = 6 > column_width
8505 }
8506 } else {
8507 word_wrapped_text = text; // repect the embedded '\n' characters
8508 }
8509
8510 auto lines = Format::split_lines(word_wrapped_text, "\n", cell.locale(),
8511 cell.is_multi_byte_character_support_enabled());
8512
8513 if (row_index - padding_top < lines.size()) {
8514 auto line = lines[row_index - padding_top];
8515
8516 // Print left padding characters
8517 stream << std::string(padding_left, ' ');
8518
8519 // Print word-wrapped line
8520 line = Format::trim(line);
8521 auto line_with_padding_size =
8522 get_sequence_length(line, cell.locale(), cell.is_multi_byte_character_support_enabled()) +
8523 padding_left + padding_right;
8524 switch (*format.font_align_) {
8525 case FontAlign::left:
8526 print_content_left_aligned(stream, line, format, line_with_padding_size, column_width);
8527 break;
8528 case FontAlign::center:
8529 print_content_center_aligned(stream, line, format, line_with_padding_size, column_width);
8530 break;
8531 case FontAlign::right:
8532 print_content_right_aligned(stream, line, format, line_with_padding_size, column_width);
8533 break;
8534 }
8535
8536 // Print right padding characters
8537 stream << std::string(padding_right, ' ');
8538 } else
8539 stream << std::string(column_width, ' ');
8540
8541 } else {
8542 // Padding bottom
8543 stream << std::string(column_width, ' ');
8544 }
8545
8546 reset_element_style(stream);
8547
8548 if (index.second + 1 == num_columns) {
8549 // Print right border after last column
8550 if (*format.show_border_right_) {
8551 apply_element_style(stream, *format.border_right_color_,
8552 *format.border_right_background_color_, {});
8553 stream << *format.border_right_;
8554 reset_element_style(stream);
8555 }
8556 }
8557 std::locale::global(old_locale);
8558 }
8559
8560 inline bool Printer::print_cell_border_top(std::ostream &stream, TableInternal &table,
8561 const std::pair<size_t, size_t> &index,
8562 const std::pair<size_t, size_t> &dimension,
8563 size_t num_columns) {
8564 auto cell = table[index.first][index.second];
8565 auto locale = cell.locale();
8566 auto old_locale = std::locale::global(std::locale(locale));
8567 auto format = cell.format();
8568 auto column_width = dimension.second;
8569
8570 auto corner = *format.corner_top_left_;
8571 auto corner_color = *format.corner_top_left_color_;
8572 auto corner_background_color = *format.corner_top_left_background_color_;
8573 auto border_top = *format.border_top_;
8574
8575 if ((corner == "" && border_top == "") || !*format.show_border_top_)
8576 return false;
8577
8578 apply_element_style(stream, corner_color, corner_background_color, {});
8579 stream << corner;
8580 reset_element_style(stream);
8581
8582 for (size_t i = 0; i < column_width; ++i) {
8583 apply_element_style(stream, *format.border_top_color_, *format.border_top_background_color_,
8584 {});
8585 stream << border_top;
8586 reset_element_style(stream);
8587 }
8588
8589 if (index.second + 1 == num_columns) {
8590 // Print corner after last column
8591 corner = *format.corner_top_right_;
8592 corner_color = *format.corner_top_right_color_;
8593 corner_background_color = *format.corner_top_right_background_color_;
8594
8595 apply_element_style(stream, corner_color, corner_background_color, {});
8596 stream << corner;
8597 reset_element_style(stream);
8598 }
8599 std::locale::global(old_locale);
8600 return true;
8601 }
8602
8603 inline bool Printer::print_cell_border_bottom(std::ostream &stream, TableInternal &table,
8604 const std::pair<size_t, size_t> &index,
8605 const std::pair<size_t, size_t> &dimension,
8606 size_t num_columns) {
8607 auto cell = table[index.first][index.second];
8608 auto locale = cell.locale();
8609 auto old_locale = std::locale::global(std::locale(locale));
8610 auto format = cell.format();
8611 auto column_width = dimension.second;
8612
8613 auto corner = *format.corner_bottom_left_;
8614 auto corner_color = *format.corner_bottom_left_color_;
8615 auto corner_background_color = *format.corner_bottom_left_background_color_;
8616 auto border_bottom = *format.border_bottom_;
8617
8618 if ((corner == "" && border_bottom == "") || !*format.show_border_bottom_)
8619 return false;
8620
8621 apply_element_style(stream, corner_color, corner_background_color, {});
8622 stream << corner;
8623 reset_element_style(stream);
8624
8625 for (size_t i = 0; i < column_width; ++i) {
8626 apply_element_style(stream, *format.border_bottom_color_,
8627 *format.border_bottom_background_color_, {});
8628 stream << border_bottom;
8629 reset_element_style(stream);
8630 }
8631
8632 if (index.second + 1 == num_columns) {
8633 // Print corner after last column
8634 corner = *format.corner_bottom_right_;
8635 corner_color = *format.corner_bottom_right_color_;
8636 corner_background_color = *format.corner_bottom_right_background_color_;
8637
8638 apply_element_style(stream, corner_color, corner_background_color, {});
8639 stream << corner;
8640 reset_element_style(stream);
8641 }
8642 std::locale::global(old_locale);
8643 return true;
8644 }

8646} // namespace tabulate

8680#pragma once
8681// #include <tabulate/table_internal.hpp>
8682
8683#if __cplusplus >= 201703L
8684
8685#include <string_view>
8686#include <variant>
8687
8688using std::get_if;
8689using std::holds_alternative;
8690using std::variant;
8691using std::visit;
8692using std::string_view;
8693#else
8694// #include <tabulate/string_view_lite.hpp>
8695// #include <tabulate/variant_lite.hpp>
8696using nonstd::get_if;
8697using nonstd::holds_alternative;
8698using nonstd::variant;
8699using nonstd::visit;
8700using nonstd::string_view;
8701#endif
8702
8703#include <utility>
8704
8705namespace tabulate {
8706
8707 class Table {
8708 public:
8709 Table() : table_(TableInternal::create()) {}
8710
8711 using Row_t = std::vector<variant<std::string, const char *, string_view, Table>>;
8712
8713 Table &add_row(const Row_t &cells) {
8714
8715 if (rows_ == 0) {
8716 // This is the first row added
8717 // cells.size() is the number of columns
8718 cols_ = cells.size();
8719 }
8720
8721 std::vector<std::string> cell_strings;
8722 if (cells.size() < cols_) {
8723 cell_strings.resize(cols_);
8724 std::fill(cell_strings.begin(), cell_strings.end(), "");
8725 } else {
8726 cell_strings.resize(cells.size());
8727 std::fill(cell_strings.begin(), cell_strings.end(), "");
8728 }
8729
8730 for (size_t i = 0; i < cells.size(); ++i) {
8731 auto cell = cells[i];
8732 if (holds_alternative<std::string>(cell)) {
8733 cell_strings[i] = *get_if<std::string>(&cell);
8734 } else if (holds_alternative<const char *>(cell)) {
8735 cell_strings[i] = *get_if<const char *>(&cell);
8736 } else if (holds_alternative<string_view>(cell)) {
8737 cell_strings[i] = std::string{*get_if<string_view>(&cell)};
8738 } else {
8739 auto table = *get_if<Table>(&cell);
8740 std::stringstream stream;
8741 table.print(stream);
8742 cell_strings[i] = stream.str();
8743 }
8744 }
8745
8746 table_->add_row(cell_strings);
8747 rows_ += 1;
8748 return *this;
8749 }
8750
8751 Row &operator[](size_t index) { return row(index); }
8752
8753 Row &row(size_t index) { return (*table_)[index]; }
8754
8755 Column column(size_t index) { return table_->column(index); }
8756
8757 Format &format() { return table_->format(); }
8758
8759 void print(std::ostream &stream) { table_->print(stream); }
8760
8761 std::string str() {
8762 std::stringstream stream;
8763 print(stream);
8764 return stream.str();
8765 }
8766
8767 std::pair<size_t, size_t> shape() { return table_->shape(); }
8768
8769 class RowIterator {
8770 public:
8771 explicit RowIterator(std::vector<std::shared_ptr<Row>>::iterator ptr) : ptr(ptr) {}
8772
8773 RowIterator operator++() {
8774 ++ptr;
8775 return *this;
8776 }
8777
8778 bool operator!=(const RowIterator &other) const { return ptr != other.ptr; }
8779
8780 Row &operator*() { return **ptr; }
8781
8782 private:
8783 std::vector<std::shared_ptr<Row>>::iterator ptr;
8784 };
8785
8786 auto begin() -> RowIterator { return RowIterator(table_->rows_.begin()); }
8787
8788 auto end() -> RowIterator { return RowIterator(table_->rows_.end()); }
8789
8790 private:
8791 friend class MarkdownExporter;
8792
8793 friend class LatexExporter;
8794
8795 friend class AsciiDocExporter;
8796
8797 friend std::ostream &operator<<(std::ostream &stream, const Table &table);
8798
8799 size_t rows_{0};
8800 size_t cols_{0};
8801 std::shared_ptr<TableInternal> table_;
8802 };
8803
8804 inline std::ostream &operator<<(std::ostream &stream, const Table &table) {
8805 const_cast<Table &>(table).print(stream);
8806 return stream;
8807 }
8808
8809} // namespace tabulate

8891#pragma once
8892// #include <tabulate/exporter.hpp>
8893
8894namespace tabulate {
8895
8896 class MarkdownExporter : public Exporter {
8897 public:
8898 std::string dump(Table &table) override {
8899 std::string result{""};
8900 apply_markdown_format(table);
8901 result = table.str();
8902 restore_table_format(table);
8903 return result;
8904 }
8905
8906 virtual ~MarkdownExporter() {}
8907
8908 private:
8909 void add_alignment_header_row(Table &table) {
8910 auto &rows = table.table_->rows_;
8911
8912 if (rows.size() >= 1) {
8913 auto alignment_row = std::make_shared<Row>(table.table_->shared_from_this());
8914
8915 // Create alignment header cells
8916 std::vector<std::string> alignment_cells{};
8917 for (auto &cell: table[0]) {
8918 auto format = cell.format();
8919 if (format.font_align_.value() == FontAlign::left) {
8920 alignment_cells.push_back(":----");
8921 } else if (format.font_align_.value() == FontAlign::center) {
8922 alignment_cells.push_back(":---:");
8923 } else if (format.font_align_.value() == FontAlign::right) {
8924 alignment_cells.push_back("----:");
8925 }
8926 }
8927
8928 // Add alignment header cells to alignment row
8929 for (auto &c: alignment_cells) {
8930 auto cell = std::make_shared<Cell>(alignment_row);
8931 cell->format()
8932 .hide_border_top()
8933 .hide_border_bottom()
8934 .border_left("|")
8935 .border_right("|")
8936 .column_separator("|")
8937 .corner("|");
8938 cell->set_text(c);
8939 if (c == ":---:")
8940 cell->format().font_align(FontAlign::center);
8941 else if (c == "----:")
8942 cell->format().font_align(FontAlign::right);
8943 alignment_row->add_cell(cell);
8944 }
8945
8946 // Insert alignment header row
8947 if (rows.size() > 1)
8948 rows.insert(rows.begin() + 1, alignment_row);
8949 else
8950 rows.push_back(alignment_row);
8951 }
8952 }
8953
8954 void remove_alignment_header_row(Table &table) {
8955 auto &rows = table.table_->rows_;
8956 table.table_->rows_.erase(rows.begin() + 1);
8957 }
8958
8959 void apply_markdown_format(Table &table) {
8960 // Apply markdown format to cells in each row
8961 for (auto row: table) {
8962 for (auto &cell: row) {
8963 auto format = cell.format();
8964 formats_.push_back(format);
8965 cell.format()
8966 .hide_border_top()
8967 .hide_border_bottom()
8968 .border_left("|")
8969 .border_right("|")
8970 .column_separator("|")
8971 .corner("|");
8972 }
8973 }
8974 // Add alignment header row at position 1
8975 add_alignment_header_row(table);
8976 }
8977
8978 void restore_table_format(Table &table) {
8979 // Remove alignment header row at position 1
8980 remove_alignment_header_row(table);
8981
8982 // Restore original formatting for each cell
8983 size_t format_index{0};
8984 for (auto row: table) {
8985 for (auto &cell: row) {
8986 cell.format() = formats_[format_index];
8987 format_index += 1;
8988 }
8989 }
8990 }
8991
8992 std::vector<Format> formats_;
8993 };
8994
8995} // namespace tabulate

9029#pragma once
9030// #include <tabulate/exporter.hpp>
9031
9032#if __cplusplus >= 201703L
9033
9034#include <optional>
9035
9036using std::optional;
9037#else
9038// #include <tabulate/optional_lite.hpp>
9039using nonstd::optional;
9040#endif
9041
9042namespace tabulate {
9043
9044 class LatexExporter : public Exporter {
9045
9046 static const char new_line = '\n';
9047
9048 public:
9049 class ExportOptions {
9050 public:
9051 ExportOptions &indentation(std::size_t value) {
9052 indentation_ = value;
9053 return *this;
9054 }
9055
9056 private:
9057 friend class LatexExporter;
9058
9059 optional<size_t> indentation_;
9060 };
9061
9062 ExportOptions &configure() { return options_; }
9063
9064 std::string dump(Table &table) override {
9065 std::string result{"\\begin{tabular}"};
9066 result += new_line;
9067
9068 result += add_alignment_header(table);
9069 result += new_line;
9070 const auto rows = table.rows_;
9071 // iterate content and put text into the table.
9072 for (size_t i = 0; i < rows; i++) {
9073 auto &row = table[i];
9074 // apply row content indentation
9075 if (options_.indentation_.has_value()) {
9076 result += std::string(options_.indentation_.value(), ' ');
9077 }
9078
9079 for (size_t j = 0; j < row.size(); j++) {
9080
9081 result += row[j].get_text();
9082
9083 // check column position, need "\\" at the end of each row
9084 if (j < row.size() - 1) {
9085 result += " & ";
9086 } else {
9087 result += " \\\\";
9088 }
9089 }
9090 result += new_line;
9091 }
9092
9093 result += "\\end{tabular}";
9094 return result;
9095 }
9096
9097 virtual ~LatexExporter() {}
9098
9099 private:
9100 std::string add_alignment_header(Table &table) {
9101 std::string result{"{"};
9102
9103 for (auto &cell: table[0]) {
9104 auto format = cell.format();
9105 if (format.font_align_.value() == FontAlign::left) {
9106 result += 'l';
9107 } else if (format.font_align_.value() == FontAlign::center) {
9108 result += 'c';
9109 } else if (format.font_align_.value() == FontAlign::right) {
9110 result += 'r';
9111 }
9112 }
9113
9114 result += "}";
9115 return result;
9116 }
9117
9118 ExportOptions options_;
9119 };
9120
9121} // namespace tabulate

9155#pragma once
9156
9157#include <algorithm>
9158#include <optional>
9159#include <sstream>
9160#include <string>
9161// #include <tabulate/exporter.hpp>
9162
9163namespace tabulate {
9164
9165 class AsciiDocExporter : public Exporter {
9166
9167 static const char new_line = '\n';
9168
9169 public:
9170 std::string dump(Table &table) override {
9171 std::stringstream ss;
9172 ss << add_alignment_header(table);
9173 ss << new_line;
9174
9175 const auto rows = table.rows_;
9176 // iterate content and put text into the table.
9177 for (size_t row_index = 0; row_index < rows; row_index++) {
9178 auto &row = table[row_index];
9179
9180 for (size_t cell_index = 0; cell_index < row.size(); cell_index++) {
9181 ss << "|";
9182 ss << add_formatted_cell(row[cell_index]);
9183 }
9184 ss << new_line;
9185 if (row_index == 0) {
9186 ss << new_line;
9187 }
9188 }
9189
9190 ss << "|===";
9191 return ss.str();
9192 }
9193
9194 virtual ~AsciiDocExporter() {}
9195
9196 private:
9197 std::string add_formatted_cell(Cell &cell) const {
9198 std::stringstream ss;
9199 auto format = cell.format();
9200 std::string cell_string = cell.get_text();
9201
9202 auto font_style = format.font_style_.value();
9203
9204 bool format_bold = false;
9205 bool format_italic = false;
9206 std::for_each(font_style.begin(), font_style.end(), [&](FontStyle &style) {
9207 if (style == FontStyle::bold) {
9208 format_bold = true;
9209 } else if (style == FontStyle::italic) {
9210 format_italic = true;
9211 }
9212 });
9213
9214 if (format_bold) {
9215 ss << '*';
9216 }
9217 if (format_italic) {
9218 ss << '_';
9219 }
9220
9221 ss << cell_string;
9222 if (format_italic) {
9223 ss << '_';
9224 }
9225 if (format_bold) {
9226 ss << '*';
9227 }
9228 return ss.str();
9229 }
9230
9231 std::string add_alignment_header(Table &table) {
9232 std::stringstream ss;
9233 ss << (R"([cols=")");
9234
9235 size_t column_count = table[0].size();
9236 size_t column_index = 0;
9237 for (auto &cell: table[0]) {
9238 auto format = cell.format();
9239
9240 if (format.font_align_.value() == FontAlign::left) {
9241 ss << '<';
9242 } else if (format.font_align_.value() == FontAlign::center) {
9243 ss << '^';
9244 } else if (format.font_align_.value() == FontAlign::right) {
9245 ss << '>';
9246 }
9247
9248 ++column_index;
9249 if (column_index != column_count) {
9250 ss << ",";
9251 }
9252 }
9253
9254 ss << R"("])";
9255 ss << new_line;
9256 ss << "|===";
9257
9258 return ss.str();
9259 }
9260 };
9261
9262} // namespace tabulate
9263
